RACE.FOOTNOTES: ORPHAN HALLIE had a good spot inside watching the contesting trio up front, was ridden hard to go after the leaders at the quarter pole, surged up the fence with an eighth remaining and won the nod for the victory at the line. HARDWARE GAP was shuffled between foes to trail the field at the half, shifted out to the five path seeing the field turning for home, split rivals at the furlong marker with a closing rush and lost the bob in a close photo at the finish. LUV TO WIN broke out at the start, pressed the issue outside down the backside, continued to force things running three wide on the turn, poked his nose in front in mid stretch but needed more to hold off the closers late. PRINCE SUSSEX had a nice position outside watching the threesome engage one another up front on the turn, rallied five sixteenths from home picking up the leaders to loom the threat in upper stretch and stalled running four wide to the finish. WOOD BE WILD set the pace inside while pressured by a pair of rivals on the turn, determinedly fought on until mid stretch and weakened late running on the wrong lead to the wire. ALLEN DIGGS battled for the lead between runners down the backside, continued fighting up front with runners on either side throughout the turn, still was in the hunt at the top of the stretch and retreated at the furlong marker.

LORD M was allowed to settle at the rear outside at the half mile marker, put in a mild run four wide around runners midway on the turn, was in the seven path at the top of the lane and had nothing to offer running to the wire. LIL GREEN MACHINE broke out at the start, tracked in the two path in the middle of the pack down the backside, was shuffled between foes to trail entering the turn and was not a factor running through the stretch. SIR GRAYVENSCROFT stalked on the rail down the backstretch, saved ground running inside on the turn, was hard ridden at the quarter pole, no response and was empty for the stretch drive.

MR CROWLEY tracked the front pair into the turn, took closer order to the top duo rallying three wide two furlongs left to run, had dead aim on the winner at the top of the stretch outside and was gaining slowly but could not wear down the winner in the end. DESOLATOR rated in the middle of a spread out field down the backside, was nudged to keep up inside on the turn, could not match strides with others and was not a presence in the stretch drive. DRAGON'S BREW settled near the back inside at the half, saved ground while advancing on the turn, was in with a chance for a small share of the prize turning for home but could not quicken inside late to be a factor. HIT THE POINT travelled at the back outside runners in the beginning, continued to trail on the turn making little progress and could not make an impression running to the wire.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SOUPER WATSON was unhurried early outside of horses, content with being near the back in the early going, put in a bold move four wide at the three eighths marker around runners to bid for the lead in upper stretch and determinedly outkicked his rival down the lane to edge away in the final stages.
